Key Match Events: Hatayaspor's offensive midfielder Vincent Aboubakar scored an early penalty kick
FC Granada playmaker Martin Hongla doubled the advantage in the 39th minute
Harambee Stars' Michael Olunga scored for Kenya in the 41st minute
Brentford FC's Brian Mbeumo stretched Cameroon's lead two minutes later
Okhdood Club's Christian Bassogog scored the final goal for Cameroon in the 55th minute
Post-Match Reflections: Kenya's hopes of earning a spot in the 2025 Africa Cup of Nations were severely damaged
The encounter proved to be a one-sided affair with Cameroon dominating possession and passing
Miscellaneous Highlights: Cameroon's dominance over Kenya stretched to five wins in nine encounters since 1972
Kenya had only two shots on target while Cameroon had five
